{"id":"2207.01998","submitter":"Markus Holzmann","authors":"Jussi Behrndt, Markus Holzmann, Georg Stenzel","title":"Schr\\\"odinger operators with oblique transmission conditions in\n  $\\mathbb{R}^2$","comments":"16 pages; to appear in Comm. Math. Phys","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1007/s00220-023-04708-7","report-no":null,"categories":"math.SP math-ph math.AP math.FA math.MP","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  In this paper we study the spectrum of self-adjoint Schr\\\"odinger operators\nin $L^2(\\mathbb{R}^2)$ with a new type of transmission conditions along a\nsmooth closed curve $\\Sigma\\subseteq \\mathbb{R}^2$. Although these\n$\\textit{oblique}$ transmission conditions are formally similar to\n$\\delta'$-conditions on $\\Sigma$ (instead of the normal derivative here the\nWirtinger derivative is used) the spectral properties are significantly\ndifferent: it turns out that for attractive interaction strengths the discrete\nspectrum is always unbounded from below. Besides this unexpected spectral\neffect we also identify the essential spectrum, and we prove a Krein-type\nresolvent formula and a Birman-Schwinger principle. Furthermore, we show that\nthese Schr\\\"odinger operators with oblique transmission conditions arise\nnaturally as non-relativistic limits of Dirac operators with electrostatic and\nLorentz scalar $\\delta$-interactions justifying their usage as models in\nquantum mechanics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Jul 2022 12:33:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 27 Mar 2023 09:37:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-17"}
