 the first orbital period distribution for hot\nsubdwarfs with cool, low-mass stellar or substellar systems selected from light\nvariations instead of radial velocity variations. It shows a period\ndistribution from 1.5 hours to 35 hours compared to the distribution of hot\nsubdwarfs with white dwarfs, which ranges from 1 hour to 30 days. These period\ndistributions can be used to constrain the previous common envelope phase.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Jul 2022 12:38:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-26"}
